{{Infobox writer | name = Anu Elizabeth Jose | image = | caption =Anu Elizabeth Jose Lyricist | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = [[Alappuzha]] | residence = [[Kochi]] | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = Lyricist | nationality = [[India]]n | years active = 2012 present | genre = | subject = malayalam | notableworks =[[Muthuchippi Poloru]], [[Thattathin Marayathu]] | partner = | children = | influences = | influenced = | awards = | signature = | website = [http://www.facebook.com/anu.e.jose/ Anu Elizabeth Jose Official Facebook Page] }} '''Anu Elizabeth Jose''' (അനു എലിസബത്ത് ജോസ്) is an [[India]]n [[lyricist]] . She made her debut in the 2012 [[Malayalam]] [[film]] ''[[Thattathin Marayathu]]'' through the evergreen hit song [[Muthuchippi Poloru]]. The film was directed by [[Vineeth Sreenivasan]] and the music was scored by [[Shaan Rahman]]
==Early life== Anu Elizabeth was born to Jose Savior and Mariyamma Jose in [[Alappuzha]] district of [[keralam|Kerala]] and grew up in [[Edappally]], [[Kochi]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Anu Elizabeth Jose biograbhy'|url=http://www.m3db.com/artists/28575}}</ref> Anu studied at the [[Federal Institute of Science and Technology]] [[Angamaly]]. She is currently working in [[Tata Consultancy Services]]. She has written more than 25 songs for 11 films.<ref>{{cite news|title= list of songs by Anu elizabeth'|url=http://www.malayalachalachithram.com/listsongs.php?l=9868}}</ref> In 2015 she had written lyrics for movie [[32aam adhyayam 23aam vaakyam]] music composed by [[Bijibal]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Omalkanmani song'|url = https://m.youtube.com/watch?_e_pi_=7%2CPAGE_ID10%2C2676905237}}</ref>
