'''Lyngam''' is an [[Austroasiatic]] language of [[Northeast India]] closely related to [[Khasi language|Khasi]]. Once listed as a dialect of [[Khasi language|Khasi]], Lyngam has in recent literature been classified as a distinct language. Lyngam speakers have food and dress similar to the neighboring [[Garo people|Garo]] people.

