The main difference with the Khasi language is that Lyngngam does not possess the voiced aspirated series. Furthermore, Lyngngam does not have the phoneme {{IPA|/ç/}}. Words which have {{IPA|/ç/}} in Khasi typically have {{IPA|/c/}} or {{IPA|/s/}} in Lyngngam,<ref name="nagaraj sect 2">{{harvnb|Nagaraja|1996|loc = sect. 2}}</ref> as in the following pairs of [[cognate]]s:
